SIMPLE: professor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Professor
<hw>Pro*fess"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a teacher, a
public teacher: cf. F. <ets>professeur</ets>. See
<er>Profess</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who professed, or makes
open declaration of, his sentiments or opinions; especially, one who
makes a public avowal of his belief in the Scriptures and his faith in
Christ, and thus unites himself to the visible church.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Professors</xex> of religion.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who professed, or publicly teaches, any science
or branch of learning; especially, an officer in a university, college,
or other seminary, whose business it is to read lectures, or instruct
students, in a particular branch of learning; as a <xex>professor</xex>
of theology, of botany, of mathematics, or of political
economy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Professorial</ent>⟦br⟧
